byline.original: By RANYA KADRI and ETHAN BRONNER
byline.contributor: Ranya Kadri reported from Amman, and Ethan Bronner from Jerusalem.

abstract: King Abdullah II of Jordan fires his government in response to public pressure for faster political reform; appoints Awn Khasawneh, an international judge, as his new prime minister.
